rawContent:
"Billy is on his way to his very own tiny home. I’m about to die with happiness!!" said Jenn Coon, a housing specialist at Blanchet House. 

She worked the phone for two days with help from fireman Matthew Silva to find Billy, 63, a long-term shelter. "He's just the nicest man," Jenn added.

Billy spent three nights sleeping outside before Jenn met him. She first called emergency shelters but they were all full. Billy was hoping for permanent shelter because he has many medical appointments. There is such a need for no-income housing in Portland. We have elder citizens living on the streets. They don't want to go to crowded shelters only to be kicked out in the morning. They need long-term shelter now.

Billy gave his permission to share his story and photo.
